atEnvMonv2.name: atEnvMonv2

revisions.description: Added chassis switch (e.g. SBx8100) descriptions to stack-related MIB objects
MIB revision history dates in descriptions updated.
OID of atEnvMonv2Traps reverted to 5 but deprecated. Added atEnvMonv2Notifications
Changed the OID value of atEnvMonv2Traps from 5 to 0 to meet RFC 3584 3.1
Removed recently added MIB objects that went against the original intent of the environment monitoring MIB.
Appended v2 to all object names to clarify version number of this mib.

atEnvMonv2.description: The AT Environment Monitoring v2 MIB for managing and reporting data relating to voltage rails, fan speeds, temperature sensors and power supply units.

AtEnvMonv2PsbSensorType.name: AtEnvMonv2PsbSensorType
AtEnvMonv2PsbSensorType.description: Indicates the type of a Power Supply Bay Device sensor.

atEnvMonv2FanAlarmSetNotify.name: atEnvMonv2FanAlarmSetNotify
atEnvMonv2FanAlarmSetNotify.description: A notification generated when the monitored speed of a fan drops below its lower threshold.

atEnvMonv2FanAlarmClearedNotify.name: atEnvMonv2FanAlarmClearedNotify
atEnvMonv2FanAlarmClearedNotify.description: A notification generated when the monitored speed of a fan returns to an acceptable value, the fan having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmSetNotify.name: atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmSetNotify
atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmSetNotify.description: A notification generated when the voltage of a monitored voltage rail goes out of tolerance, either by dropping below its lower threshold, or exceeding its upper threshold.

atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmClearedNotify.name: atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmClearedNotify
atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmClearedNotify.description: A notification generated when the voltage of a monitored voltage rail returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2TempAlarmSetNotify.name: atEnvMonv2TempAlarmSetNotify
atEnvMonv2TempAlarmSetNotify.description: A notification generated when a monitored temperature exceeds its upper threshold.

atEnvMonv2TempAlarmClearedNotify.name: atEnvMonv2TempAlarmClearedNotify
atEnvMonv2TempAlarmClearedNotify.description: A notification generated when a monitored temperature returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmSetNotify.name: atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmSetNotify
atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmSetNotify.description: A notification generated when a monitored parameter of a power supply bay device goes out of tolerance.

atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmClearedNotify.name: atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmClearedNotify
atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmClearedNotify.description: A notification generated when a monitored parameter of a power supply bay device returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2FanTable.name: atEnvMonv2FanTable
atEnvMonv2FanTable.description: A table of information about fans installed in the device that have their fan speeds monitored by environment monitoring hardware.

atEnvMonv2FanEntry.name: atEnvMonv2FanEntry
atEnvMonv2FanEntry.description: The description, current speed, lower threshold speed and current status of a fan.

atEnvMonv2FanStackMemberId.name: atEnvMonv2FanStackMemberId
atEnvMonv2FanStackMemberId.description: The index of the stack member hosting this fan. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID of the active controller.

atEnvMonv2FanBoardIndex.name: atEnvMonv2FanBoardIndex
atEnvMonv2FanBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this fan in the board table.

atEnvMonv2FanIndex.name: atEnvMonv2FanIndex
atEnvMonv2FanIndex.description: The numeric identifier of this fan on its host board.

atEnvMonv2FanCurrentSpeed.name: atEnvMonv2FanCurrentSpeed
atEnvMonv2FanCurrentSpeed.description: The current speed of this fan in revolutions per minute.

atEnvMonv2FanLowerThreshold.name: atEnvMonv2FanLowerThreshold
atEnvMonv2FanLowerThreshold.description: The minimum acceptable speed of the fan in revolutions per minute.

atEnvMonv2FanStatus.name: atEnvMonv2FanStatus
atEnvMonv2FanStatus.description: An indication of whether this fan is currently in an alarm condition. A value of 'failed' indicates that its current speed is too low, 'good' indicates that the current speed is acceptable.

atEnvMonv2VoltageTable.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageTable
atEnvMonv2VoltageTable.description: A table of information about voltage rails in the device that are monitored by environment monitoring hardware.

atEnvMonv2VoltageEntry.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageEntry
atEnvMonv2VoltageEntry.description: The description, current value, upper & lower threshold settings and current status of a voltage rail.

atEnvMonv2VoltageStackMemberId.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageStackMemberId
atEnvMonv2VoltageStackMemberId.description: The index of the stack member hosting this voltage sensor. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID of the active controller.

atEnvMonv2VoltageBoardIndex.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageBoardIndex
atEnvMonv2VoltageBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this voltage sensor in the board table.

atEnvMonv2VoltageIndex.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageIndex
atEnvMonv2VoltageIndex.description: The numeric identifier of this voltage rail on its host board.

atEnvMonv2VoltageDescription.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageDescription
atEnvMonv2VoltageDescription.description: The description of this voltage rail.

atEnvMonv2VoltageCurrent.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageCurrent
atEnvMonv2VoltageCurrent.description: The current reading of this voltage rail in millivolts.

atEnvMonv2VoltageUpperThreshold.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageUpperThreshold
atEnvMonv2VoltageUpperThreshold.description: The maximum acceptable reading of this voltage rail in millivolts.

atEnvMonv2VoltageLowerThreshold.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageLowerThreshold
atEnvMonv2VoltageLowerThreshold.description: The minimum acceptable reading of this voltage rail in millivolts.

atEnvMonv2VoltageStatus.name: atEnvMonv2VoltageStatus
atEnvMonv2VoltageStatus.description: An indication of whether this voltage rail is currently in an alarm condition. A value of 'outOfRange' indicates that its current reading is outside its threshold range, 'inRange' indicates that the current reading is acceptable.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureTable.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureTable
atEnvMonv2TemperatureTable.description: A table of information about temperature sensors in the device that are monitored by environment monitoring hardware.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureEntry.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureEntry
atEnvMonv2TemperatureEntry.description: The description, current value, upper threshold setting and current status of a temperature sensor.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureStackMemberId.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureStackMemberId
atEnvMonv2TemperatureStackMemberId.description: The index of the stack member hosting this temperature sensor. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID of the active controller.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureBoardIndex.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureBoardIndex
atEnvMonv2TemperatureBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this temperature sensor in the board table.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureIndex.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureIndex
atEnvMonv2TemperatureIndex.description: The numeric identifier of this temperature sensor on its host board.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureDescription.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureDescription
atEnvMonv2TemperatureDescription.description: The description of this temperature sensor.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureCurrent.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureCurrent
atEnvMonv2TemperatureCurrent.description: The current reading of this temperature sensor in tenths of a degree Celsius.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureUpperThreshold.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureUpperThreshold
atEnvMonv2TemperatureUpperThreshold.description: The maximum acceptable reading of this temperature sensor in tenths of a degree Celsius.

atEnvMonv2TemperatureStatus.name: atEnvMonv2TemperatureStatus
atEnvMonv2TemperatureStatus.description: An indication of whether this temperature sensor is currently in an alarm condition. A value of 'outOfRange' indicates that its current reading is outside its threshold range, 'inRange' indicates that the current reading is acceptable.

atEnvMonv2PsbTable.name: atEnvMonv2PsbTable
atEnvMonv2PsbTable.description: A table of information about power supply bays in the system and any devices that are installed.

atEnvMonv2PsbEntry.name: atEnvMonv2PsbEntry
atEnvMonv2PsbEntry.description: The description and current status of a power supply bay device.

atEnvMonv2PsbHostStackMemberId.name: atEnvMonv2PsbHostStackMemberId
atEnvMonv2PsbHostStackMemberId.description: The index of the stack member hosting this power supply bay. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID of the active controller.

atEnvMonv2PsbHostBoardIndex.name: atEnvMonv2PsbHostBoardIndex
atEnvMonv2PsbHostBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this power supply bay in the board table.

atEnvMonv2PsbHostSlotIndex.name: atEnvMonv2PsbHostSlotIndex
atEnvMonv2PsbHostSlotIndex.description: The index of this power supply bay on its host board. This index is fixed for each slot, on each type of board.

atEnvMonv2PsbHeldBoardIndex.name: atEnvMonv2PsbHeldBoardIndex
atEnvMonv2PsbHeldBoardIndex.description: The index of a board installed in this power supply bay. This value corresponds to atEnvMonv2PsbSensorBoardIndex for each sensor on this board. A value of 0 indicates that a board is is either not present or not supported.

atEnvMonv2PsbHeldBoardId.name: atEnvMonv2PsbHeldBoardId
atEnvMonv2PsbHeldBoardId.description: The type of board installed in this power supply bay. The values of this object are taken from the pprXxx object IDs under the boards sub-tree in the parent MIB. A value of 0 indicates that a board is either not present or not supported.

atEnvMonv2PsbDescription.name: atEnvMonv2PsbDescription
atEnvMonv2PsbDescription.description: The description of this power supply bay.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorTable.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorTable
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorTable.description: A table of information about environment monitoring sensors on devices installed in power supply bays.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorEntry.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorEntry
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorEntry.description: The description and current status of a device installed in a power supply bay.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorStackMemberId.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorStackMemberId
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorStackMemberId.description: The index of the stack member hosting this sensor. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID of the active controller.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorBoardIndex.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorBoardIndex
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorBoardIndex.description: The index of the board hosting this sensor in the board table.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorIndex.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorIndex
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorIndex.description: The index of this power supply bay environmental sensor on its host board.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorType.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorType
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorType.description: The type of environmental variable this sensor detects.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorDescription.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorDescription
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorDescription.description: The description of this power supply bay environmental sensor.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorStatus.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorStatus
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorStatus.description: An indication of whether this environmental sensor is currently in an alarm condition. A value of 'failed' indicates that the device is in a failure condition, 'good' indicates that the device is functioning normally.

atEnvMonv2PsbSensorReading.name: atEnvMonv2PsbSensorReading
atEnvMonv2PsbSensorReading.description: An indication of whether this environmental sensor is currently reading a value for the monitored device. A value of 'no' indicates that there is no current reading, 'yes' indicates that the monitored device is supplying a reading.

atEnvMonv2FanAlarmSetEvent.name: atEnvMonv2FanAlarmSetEvent
atEnvMonv2FanAlarmSetEvent.description: A trap generated when the monitored speed of a fan drops below its lower threshold.

atEnvMonv2FanAlarmClearedEvent.name: atEnvMonv2FanAlarmClearedEvent
atEnvMonv2FanAlarmClearedEvent.description: A trap generated when the monitored speed of a fan returns to an acceptable value, the fan having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmSetEvent.name: atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmSetEvent
atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmSetEvent.description: A trap generated when the voltage of a monitored voltage rail goes out of tolerance, either by dropping below its lower threshold, or exceeding its upper threshold.

atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmClearedEvent.name: atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmClearedEvent
atEnvMonv2VoltAlarmClearedEvent.description: A trap generated when the voltage of a monitored voltage rail returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2TempAlarmSetEvent.name: atEnvMonv2TempAlarmSetEvent
atEnvMonv2TempAlarmSetEvent.description: A trap generated when a monitored temperature exceeds its upper threshold.

atEnvMonv2TempAlarmClearedEvent.name: atEnvMonv2TempAlarmClearedEvent
atEnvMonv2TempAlarmClearedEvent.description: A trap generated when a monitored temperature returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmSetEvent.name: atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmSetEvent
atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmSetEvent.description: A trap generated when a monitored parameter of a power supply bay device goes out of tolerance.

atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmClearedEvent.name: atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmClearedEvent
atEnvMonv2PsbAlarmClearedEvent.description: A trap generated when a monitored parameter of a power supply bay device returns to an acceptable value, having previously been in an alarm condition.

atEnvMonv2FaultLedTable.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLedTable
atEnvMonv2FaultLedTable.description: A table of information detailing any LED fault indications on the device.

atEnvMonv2FaultLedEntry.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLedEntry
atEnvMonv2FaultLedEntry.description: An entry pertaining to a given fault LED.

atEnvMonv2FaultLedStackMemberId.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLedStackMemberId
atEnvMonv2FaultLedStackMemberId.description: The index of the stack member hosting this fault LED. For a chassis switch, it corresponds to the card ID of the active controller.

atEnvMonv2FaultLed1Flash.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLed1Flash
atEnvMonv2FaultLed1Flash.description: This object indicates whether a fault LED is currently showing a system failure by flashing once. It indicates that one or more heatsink fans have failed, or are operating below the recommended speed.

atEnvMonv2FaultLed2Flashes.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLed2Flashes
atEnvMonv2FaultLed2Flashes.description: This object indicates whether a fault LED is currently showing a system failure by flashing twice. It indicates that one or both of the chassis fans are not installed, or the fans are operating below the recommended speed.

atEnvMonv2FaultLed3Flashes.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLed3Flashes
atEnvMonv2FaultLed3Flashes.description: This object indicates whether a fault LED is currently showing a system failure by flashing three times. It indicates that the ability to monitor temperature or fans has failed.

atEnvMonv2FaultLed4Flashes.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLed4Flashes
atEnvMonv2FaultLed4Flashes.description: This object indicates whether a fault LED is currently showing a system failure by flashing four times. It indicates that an XEM failed to initialise or is incompatible.

atEnvMonv2FaultLed5Flashes.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLed5Flashes
atEnvMonv2FaultLed5Flashes.description: This object indicates whether a fault LED is currently showing a system failure by flashing five times. This flashing sequence is not currently in use.

atEnvMonv2FaultLed6Flashes.name: atEnvMonv2FaultLed6Flashes
atEnvMonv2FaultLed6Flashes.description: This object indicates whether a fault LED is currently showing a system failure by flashing six times. It indicates that the device's temperature has exceeded the recommended threshold.
